34
00:01:30,681 --> 00:01:34,786
and take the concept of a video game into true interactive entertainment.

35
00:01:36,124 --> 00:01:39,866
Now, saying emotionally engaging is easier said than done.

36
00:01:39,866 --> 00:01:42,228
All of us, probably mostly all of us,

37
00:01:42,228 --> 00:01:44,089
especially people into games,

38
00:01:44,089 --> 00:01:45,870
are constantly bombarded by media.

39
00:01:45,870 --> 00:01:48,892
Movies, TV, games, the little screens

40
00:01:48,892 --> 00:01:50,353
we have in our pockets.

41
00:01:50,353 --> 00:01:53,735
These contents are always trying to vie for our emotion.

42
00:01:53,735 --> 00:01:57,197
And what's happening over time, we get desensitized.

43
00:01:57,197 --> 00:01:59,998
We actually start creating barriers and defenses

44
00:01:59,998 --> 00:02:01,599
to push against that content,

45
00:02:01,599 --> 00:02:03,400
so pretty much we could say sane.

46
00:02:05,263 --> 00:02:08,208
So, how do we break through these barriers?

47
00:02:08,208 --> 00:02:13,077
